### 1. componentDidPatch(error, info)

react16  ErrorBoundary  lifecycle  component render  component 

** Error  lifecycle method  componentDidPatch** constructor  throw Error  componentDidCatch  catch 

`componentDidCatch`  error, info componentDidCatch fallback UI 

```jsx
class Post extends Component {
  constructor() {
    throw new Error('oops'); //  componentDidCatch
  }

  componentWillMount() {
    this.setState(state => {
      throw new Error('oops');
      return {};
    })
  }
}
class App extends Component {
  constructor() {
    super(props);
    this.state = {
      post: { content: '' }
    }
  }

  updatePost = () => {
    this.setState(state => ({ ...state, post: null }));
  }

  componentDidCatch(error, info) {
    this.setState({ hasError: true });
    Logger.warn(error, info);
  }


  render() {
    return (
      <div>
        <Post post={this.state.post} />
      </div>
    )
  }
}
```

